Description: Ostracon, fragment (two pieces joined) of the body of a light-brown pottery jar, perhaps the same vessel as 58865, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and remains of three lines of black-painted hieratic text giving three names and titles.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amarna, el-, TA:26/61 The Great Temple, The Sanctuary
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393464) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393464)
